2
00:00:49,730 --> 00:00:55,250

3
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:04,890
This b*stard was alive this whole time?

4
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:12,250
Oh Man Ok, you committed too many sins

5
00:01:12,250 --> 00:01:15,330
so you can't be convicted within the law's boundaries.

6
00:01:15,330 --> 00:01:16,330

7
00:01:16,330 --> 00:01:20,390
The drug addict, Lee Yong Deuk, killed Doo Hak's father and covered it up as an accident.

8
00:01:20,390 --> 00:01:22,640
 Directly ordering him to do so was

9
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:23,600
 Oh Man Ok.

10
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:25,980
But Oh Man Ok has no particular motive

11
00:01:25,980 --> 00:01:27,660
for killing Doo Hak's father.

12
00:01:27,660 --> 00:01:31,150
Then that means that Oh Man Ok's boss gave him the order.

13
00:01:31,150 --> 00:01:32,990
It could be the orders of just one person,

14
00:01:32,990 --> 00:01:36,270
 or it could be the will of the entire family.

15
00:01:36,270 --> 00:01:38,270
Can't we just report this to the police?

16
00:01:38,270 --> 00:01:41,710
Geez! Hey, now that you've grown a bit older,

17
00:01:41,710 --> 00:01:45,130
shouldn't your brain start working by now?

18
00:01:45,130 --> 00:01:47,680
How could the police handle "Namsan" (NSA)?

19
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:50,670
Also, who would listen to the words of a drug addict?

20
00:01:50,670 --> 00:01:51,840
Who would believe him?

21
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:54,450
Oh, you're right.

22
00:01:54,450 --> 00:01:56,230
The police couldn't handle them.

23
00:01:56,230 --> 00:01:58,470
But as Young Pil found in his background search,

24
00:01:58,470 --> 00:02:02,890
Oh Man Ok is intent filling his own belly; he even takes money from casinos.

25
00:02:02,890 --> 00:02:04,960
 Also, although he's the right-hand man of this family,

26
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:07,460
he's got a grudge against Choi Cheol Woong.

27
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:11,240
Then it's very likely that Choi Cheol Woong demoted him to Busan.

28
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:15,690
- Yes. 
 - But he was brought back right away.

29
00:02:15,690 --> 00:02:18,360
The one who brought him back was probably Hwang Choong Sung,

30
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:20,390
 since he was his long-time, right-hand man.

31
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:22,490
 I mean, Choi Cheol Woong likely couldn't do anything about it.

32
00:02:22,490 --> 00:02:27,710
More importantly, he best knows the corruption of that family.

33
00:02:27,710 --> 00:02:31,980
So it appears he decided it was best to keep him around,

34
00:02:31,980 --> 00:02:34,970
coddle him, and keep an eye on him.

35
00:02:34,970 --> 00:02:38,960
Usually, the traitor is someone who's closest to the boss or knows him well.

36
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:42,880
Really? The closest one...

37
00:02:42,880 --> 00:02:44,360
Gosh, you b*stard!

38
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:46,070
I'm just joking!

39
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:51,130
In any case, if they all stick together, we can't touch them.

40
00:02:51,130 --> 00:02:56,040
They have power, money, a prosecutor who has the right to investigate cases,

41
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:59,860
and a vicious hunting dog who wouldn't hesitate to kill.

42
00:02:59,860 --> 00:03:02,230
We need to break apart what's tightly clumped together.

43
00:03:02,230 --> 00:03:03,760
Bingo.

44
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:04,960
How?

45
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:07,480
We'll have to cause them to doubt each other.

46
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:09,770
Who? Choi Cheol Woong?

47
00:03:09,770 --> 00:03:11,320
No.

48
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:17,460
Within that group, the one who has the weakest connection

49
00:03:17,460 --> 00:03:20,030
and has the biggest greed...

50
00:03:20,030 --> 00:03:24,590

51
00:03:24,590 --> 00:03:27,600

52
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:29,780
It's the hunting dog.

53
00:03:29,780 --> 00:03:31,950
"The hunting dog."

54
00:03:37,140 --> 00:03:39,050

55
00:03:39,050 --> 00:03:40,090

56
00:03:41,650 --> 00:03:43,310
What do you mean?

57
00:03:43,310 --> 00:03:46,570
Are you saying I protected Team Captain Oh?

58
00:03:46,570 --> 00:03:48,030
Yes.

59
00:03:48,030 --> 00:03:50,340
That's what it looked like.

60
00:03:50,340 --> 00:03:53,890
Mother, does Team Leader Oh know a weakness of yours?

61
00:03:53,890 --> 00:03:56,080
What in the world are you talking about?

62
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:57,660
What weakness?

63
00:03:57,660 --> 00:03:59,200
Cheol Woong.

64
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:04,190
I know that you hate Team Captain Oh, but he sincerely apologized to you.

65
00:04:04,190 --> 00:04:07,530
Also, our family needs him.

66
00:04:08,430 --> 00:04:09,640
Do we need him?

67
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:12,080
You should forgive him now.

68
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:15,090
I mean, I suppose you would need him, Mom.

69
00:04:15,090 --> 00:04:18,370
He played a big role in helping you acquire your wealth, Mother, did he not?

70
00:04:18,370 --> 00:04:21,730
Cheol Woong, I did that for your future–

71
00:04:21,730 --> 00:04:23,960
No, no, no.

72
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:28,030
It wasn't for my future,

73
00:04:28,030 --> 00:04:31,550
but you nearly screwed up my future.

74
00:04:31,550 --> 00:04:33,780
Your real estate

75
00:04:33,780 --> 00:04:36,750
was purchased with insider knowledge of the development plans.

76
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:38,510
It's not just me.

77
00:04:38,510 --> 00:04:40,300
Everyone does it!

78
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:42,140
You know that much!

79
00:04:42,140 --> 00:04:43,910
"Everyone does it"?

80
00:04:43,910 --> 00:04:47,920
Ordinary people don't have access to such power or information.

81
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:51,020
There's no way Oh Man Ok did that for you purely out of loyalty.

82
00:04:51,020 --> 00:04:54,140
And you are not the type to leave him uncompensated, Mom.

83
00:04:54,140 --> 00:04:56,310
That will all become evidence later.

84
00:04:56,310 --> 00:04:57,780
That is necessary.

85
00:04:57,780 --> 00:04:59,390
Does a horse run only by whipping it?

86
00:04:59,390 --> 00:05:01,370
It also needs to be given carrots to run!

87
00:05:01,370 --> 00:05:06,170
That's because a horse is a beast that can be tamed.

88
00:05:06,170 --> 00:05:10,700
Oh Man Ok is not a beast you can tame, Mom.

89
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:12,790
Cheol Woong.

90
00:05:12,790 --> 00:05:15,630
We have your father.

91
00:05:15,630 --> 00:05:20,520
Team Captain Oh can't do whatever he wants against us or betray us.

92
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:25,150
Everything that Oh Man Ok knows about us,

93
00:05:25,150 --> 00:05:29,760
that will all be a deadly weapon that he can use against us, Mom!

94
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:33,430
Cheol Woong. Why are you being like this?

95
00:05:33,430 --> 00:05:38,320
Your father, you, and I all agreed to move past this already.

96
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:40,960
Let's stop this now, please?

97
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:45,830
Oh Man Ok threatened me before,

98
00:05:45,830 --> 00:05:47,300
in this very spot.

99
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:48,650
What?

100
00:05:48,650 --> 00:05:51,050
He threatened me,

101
00:05:51,050 --> 00:05:55,700
knowing that I murdered someone and had Doo Hak take the blame.

102
00:06:00,130 --> 00:06:01,430
And...

103
00:06:02,230 --> 00:06:04,390
And what else did he threaten you with?

104
00:06:05,590 --> 00:06:09,480
 And you killed a crucial witness to that,

105
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:12,780
 via the closest person to you.

106
00:06:14,860 --> 00:06:18,410
I'm asking just in case,

107
00:06:19,210 --> 00:06:21,200
about Ahjussi Joong Ho...

108
00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:24,200
were you responsible, Mom?

109
00:06:26,050 --> 00:06:28,690
What are you talking about?

110
00:06:28,690 --> 00:06:32,520
Are you trying to say that I ordered him to kill Ahjussi?

111
00:06:34,170 --> 00:06:37,230
That was an accident!

112
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:41,270
If you weren't responsible, then tell me so.

113
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:45,330
Don't look at me with those eyes!

114
00:06:45,330 --> 00:06:47,650
It's not me.

115
00:06:47,650 --> 00:06:49,240
I'm not responsible for that!

116
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:51,390
Then...

117
00:06:51,390 --> 00:06:52,900
was it Father?

118
00:06:52,900 --> 00:06:54,400
Cheol Woong.

119
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:57,450
Tell me the truth, Mom.

120
00:06:58,950 --> 00:07:03,050
Do you know what that guy said to me?

121
00:07:03,050 --> 00:07:07,100
He said the one closest to me did it.

122
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:10,960
So please tell me the truth.

123
00:07:12,090 --> 00:07:14,610
Lee Joong Ho threatened your mother.

124
00:07:14,610 --> 00:07:16,390
Honey...

125
00:07:17,750 --> 00:07:21,070
- Excuse me? 
 - While Team Captain Oh was acting as your mother's security,

126
00:07:21,070 --> 00:07:23,940
he found out about Lee Joong Ho's threats.

127
00:07:23,940 --> 00:07:28,460
I found out later after receiving his report that he took care of it by himself.

128
00:07:30,670 --> 00:07:32,390
Does that make any sense?

129
00:07:32,390 --> 00:07:34,150
How could Team Captain Oh do that by himself?

130
00:07:34,150 --> 00:07:37,260
There are times in our field when we act first then report later.

131
00:07:37,260 --> 00:07:38,270
You know that as well.

132
00:07:38,270 --> 00:07:39,550
But even so, that is a bit–

133
00:07:39,550 --> 00:07:41,590
Don't make this a problem anymore!

134
00:07:41,590 --> 00:07:44,850
You can't make this a problem, and you shouldn't either.

135
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:49,760
Do you want the truth?

136
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:55,940
The truth is... knowing the truth is not always right and worthwhile.

137
00:07:55,940 --> 00:08:00,830
An uncomfortable truth can actually cause chaos in society and destroy a nation.

138
00:08:00,830 --> 00:08:03,050
At times, it is often

139
00:08:03,050 --> 00:08:05,750
more worthwhile not to know or right to cover it up.

140
00:08:05,750 --> 00:08:09,690
But if you still feel you must know the truth, go ahead and try it.

141
00:08:09,690 --> 00:08:14,230
In return, you will have to lay everything down:

142
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:18,630
your ambitions and your love.

143
00:08:44,460 --> 00:08:46,930
I was so shocked as well.

144
00:08:48,230 --> 00:08:51,330
I didn't know Team Captain Oh would go to that extent.

145
00:08:53,730 --> 00:08:55,710
Did Ahjussi...

146
00:08:56,710 --> 00:08:59,270
really demand money from you?

147
00:09:00,170 --> 00:09:01,990
Yes.

148
00:09:03,190 --> 00:09:05,400
And did you give it to him?

149
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:09,440
That real estate agency Doo Hak's mother is running

150
00:09:11,140 --> 00:09:13,850
got started using my money.

151
00:09:14,650 --> 00:09:16,730
It's the truth.

152
00:09:30,700 --> 00:09:32,500
Honestly,

153
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:35,980
I can't believe it.

154
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:39,690
He's not someone who would do that.

155
00:09:39,690 --> 00:09:42,030
I felt the same way.

156
00:09:43,830 --> 00:09:47,380
I guess it was hard for him to come here without any money.

157
00:09:47,380 --> 00:09:49,300
He was like...

158
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:54,730
a real father to me.

159
00:09:54,730 --> 00:09:56,470
I know.

160
00:09:58,040 --> 00:10:03,870
Even more the reason I couldn't tell you the truth.

161
00:10:36,310 --> 00:10:38,860
 When I look at you, Cheol Woong,

162
00:10:38,860 --> 00:10:42,770
 you take after your grandfather.

163
00:10:43,570 --> 00:10:46,960
 You will become a great person

164
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:49,830
 just like your grandfather.

165
00:10:49,830 --> 00:10:53,920
 Well... If I could be like him in the slightest, I would be happy.

166
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:56,930
 Aigoo, how you're also humble!

167
00:10:56,930 --> 00:11:00,550
 You are truly an adult, really.

168
00:11:00,550 --> 00:11:02,300
 Cheol Woong.

169
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:05,540
 Let me give you a hug.

170
00:11:31,420 --> 00:11:33,220

171
00:11:35,530 --> 00:11:36,660
Hello?

172
00:11:36,660 --> 00:11:38,350
 It's me.

173
00:11:38,350 --> 00:11:42,280
If you still can't believe me, you can ask Cheol Woong yourself.

174
00:11:42,280 --> 00:11:45,030
Would Cheol Woong admit it even if I asked him?

175
00:11:45,030 --> 00:11:48,260
Who would admit to being a murderer, especially without evidence?

176
00:11:49,260 --> 00:11:50,830
Doo Hak, please–

177
00:11:50,830 --> 00:11:54,490
You can think I am spewing nonsense out of vengeance.

178
00:11:54,490 --> 00:12:00,260
Remember what I said to you before I got shot and jumped in the ocean?

179
00:12:00,260 --> 00:12:03,300
 Listen carefully to what I'm about to say.

180
00:12:03,300 --> 00:12:06,560
 There's a slush fund ledger I gave to the NSA.

181
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:08,990
 If that's revealed to the world...

182
00:12:08,990 --> 00:12:11,080
That...

183
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:12,720
You still have it, right?

184
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:14,250
Yes, I remember it.

185
00:12:14,250 --> 00:12:15,490
Why do you ask about that?

186
00:12:15,490 --> 00:12:18,240
You said not to open it or show it to anyone.

187
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:21,030
Because it's so dangerous, and you would get hurt.

188
00:12:21,030 --> 00:12:25,590
I wouldn't be around so you had no one to protect you.

189
00:12:26,590 --> 00:12:28,960
Within the slush fund ledger,

190
00:12:29,610 --> 00:12:31,920
there is a notebook.

191
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:33,280
Yes.

192
00:12:34,060 --> 00:12:36,300
I can say it.

193
00:12:36,300 --> 00:12:38,020
I can say it's not true.

194
00:12:38,020 --> 00:12:40,920
Even if I die and meet those two,

195
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:43,870
I can say it's not true!

196
00:12:49,180 --> 00:12:52,450
Even if such ridiculous things took place,

197
00:12:52,450 --> 00:12:55,510
would Hyung Doo Hak live not saying anything?

198
00:12:55,510 --> 00:12:58,000
What kind of crazy b*stard

199
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:00,960
would live such a long sentence in prison for someone else, Jung Shin?

200
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:04,290
- Isn't that right? 
 - That's right.

201
00:13:04,290 --> 00:13:07,090
Lee Doo Hak sure happens to be a crazy fool.

202
00:13:07,090 --> 00:13:08,660
Choi Cheol Woong.

203
00:13:08,660 --> 00:13:11,780
You were such a good friend to me,

204
00:13:11,780 --> 00:13:13,850
and a friend I felt bad for.

205
00:13:15,250 --> 00:13:18,080
I really hoped it wasn't you.

206
00:13:19,130 --> 00:13:20,320

207
00:13:55,830 --> 00:13:57,410

208
00:14:02,020 --> 00:14:05,120

209
00:14:11,640 --> 00:14:14,720

210
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:20,920

211
00:14:23,870 --> 00:14:25,720
 That day,

212
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:28,420
 it was pouring raining so heavily.

213
00:14:29,150 --> 00:14:32,360
 My father returned from Cheol Woong's house completely soaked.

214
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:34,240
 Doo Hak.

215
00:14:34,880 --> 00:14:38,720
 He looked down at me while I was crouching under the eaves,

216
00:14:41,050 --> 00:14:43,430
 with such a pitiful look in his eyes.

217
00:14:44,230 --> 00:14:45,830
 And...

218
00:14:46,830 --> 00:14:49,410
 with a gaze showing he had no choice,

219
00:14:51,300 --> 00:14:55,900
 he said I should go to jail instead of Cheol Woong,

220
00:14:58,140 --> 00:15:01,710
 and I shouldn't forgive my father.

221
00:15:03,470 --> 00:15:08,550
 Jung Shin was looking down at me in disbelief.

222
00:15:08,550 --> 00:15:11,250
 And she kept asking me,

223
00:15:11,250 --> 00:15:13,230
 holding onto me.

224
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:17,860
 I couldn't say anything.

225
00:15:18,970 --> 00:15:21,340
 In the police car on the way to the station,

226
00:15:21,340 --> 00:15:24,380
 Cheol Woong told me he was sorry.

227
00:15:24,380 --> 00:15:26,460
 I answered him saying,

228
00:15:26,460 --> 00:15:28,660
 "What are you sorry about?"

229
00:15:28,660 --> 00:15:31,830
 "You are human, while I'm the son of a servant."

230
00:15:31,830 --> 00:15:35,830
 "I'm pretty much a dog or a pig so what are you sorry about?"

231
00:15:35,830 --> 00:15:39,810
 And like that, I came here.

232
00:15:39,810 --> 00:15:44,250
 The son of a servant dreamed a useless dream.

233
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:46,740
 I dreamed of becoming a Korean Literature teacher,

234
00:15:46,740 --> 00:15:51,650
 and of eating dinner with Jung Shin, who looks pretty with her pigtails

235
00:15:51,650 --> 00:15:55,060
 when I come home from work.

236
00:15:55,660 --> 00:16:00,050
 That was a ridiculous ambition.

237
00:16:00,050 --> 00:16:03,300
 How dare Lee Doo Hak, the son of a servant,

238
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:05,960
 nothing more than a dog or a pig...

